## Remote command endpoints

Each endpoint runs a command on a remote target via SSH. Call as
`exec_{slug}.run(command, args?, opts?)` inside `run_js`. Returns
`{stdout, stderr, exitCode, durationMs}` (strings + numbers). Non-zero
exit codes are not errors — inspect `exitCode` and `stderr`. Buffered
to 20 MiB per stream; if you need more, ask the agent author to expose
a typed Go tool that wraps the streaming primitive.

Put shell features (pipes, redirection) in `command`; use `args` for
safe multi-arg invocation (args are quoted before being sent to the
remote shell):

```javascript
exec_ci.run("kick-build", ["--branch", "main"])
exec_vps.run("kubectl get pods -o json | jq '.items[] | .metadata.name'")
```
