## Storage directories

These are the S3 paths you can touch on this run. `read` lets you `fileRead`/`fileReadBytes`/`fileStat`; `write` lets you `fileWrite`/`fileDelete`; `list` lets you `fileList`. A `-` means you don't have that cap. Paths are slashless prefixes (no leading `/`, no trailing `/`) — join with a filename like `reports/q1.csv`.

**Scoped directories** carry an extra segment in the path so each caller (user / conversation / one tool call) has its own isolated slot — e.g. `<dir>/user-<id>/...`. You never construct the scope segment yourself; `fileWrite("<dir>/foo.jpg", ...)` returns the scoped path, and the path you receive is the path you read back with. Don't strip or substitute scope segments — they're the access ticket.
